# Multi-Agent Web Agency Controller — Cursor Rules

## Project Identity
- **Name:** Multi-Agent Web Agency Controller
- **Repo:** https://github.com/digitex-erp/Multi-Agent-Web-Agency
- **Vision:** [PROJECT-CONCEPT.md](./PROJECT-CONCEPT.md)
- **Work list:** [TODO.md](./TODO.md) · **Cursor blueprint:** [PLAN.md](./PLAN.md)
- **No payment gateway** — billing is offline ($400/mo retainer model)

## Technical Stack
- **Language:** TypeScript (strict interfaces, explicit types)
- **Frontend:** React 19, Vite 6, Tailwind CSS 4, motion/react, lucide-react only (no custom SVGs)
- **Backend:** Express 4 on port 3000, tsx for dev, esbuild bundle for prod
- **AI:** **LangGraph** orchestration — Python `ChatNVIDIA` (primary) + TypeScript LangGraph (fallback on Vercel)
- **Audits:** Lighthouse CLI + Chrome — no Google PageSpeed API key
- **Target DB:** Supabase PostgreSQL (not yet wired)
- **Target orchestration:** LangGraph Python (not yet wired)

## Typography
- UI: Inter (sans)
- Headings: Space Grotesk
- Metrics / logs: JetBrains Mono

## Architecture Rules
- Keep UI modular — avoid bloating App.tsx or single 1000+ line files when refactoring
- External API calls **only** in Express routes or `src/lib/*` services imported by server.ts
- Never expose API keys in client bundles
- Replace hardcoded mock data with database services as TODO phases complete
- HITL gates must block HeyGen and outreach until human approval
- Outreach must use Comment-to-DM (Meta Graph) or SMTP — never unsolicited cold IG DMs
- PSI audits: Lighthouse local queue, max 4 concurrent by default (`LIGHTHOUSE_MAX_CONCURRENT`)

## Code Standards
- Touch targets ≥ 44px on mobile (`min-h-11`, `min-w-11`)
- Use `{ data, error }` or typed API responses with `success` boolean
- Match existing Tailwind patterns: slate/indigo/emerald palette, rounded-xl cards
- Prefer minimal diffs — one phase at a time per TODO.md

## When Adding Features
1. Update TODO.md step status (⬜ → 🟡 → ✅)
2. Add env vars to `.env.example` with comments
3. Document new API routes in README.md
4. Wire SystemMetrics when adding external API integrations
